news.title: Jaiprakash Associates partners with Gulshan Homz, CRC to complete over 600 flats in Noida
news.para: ​To fulfill its commitment to customers, Jaiprakash Associates Ltd said it has "entered into multiple joint working arrangement" with real estate developers Gulshan Homz group of companies and CRC to complete and hand over 619 high-end Golf apartments in Jaypee Greens Wish Town Noida.

news.title: Delhi Metro upgrading conventional light system with LED lights
news.para: This is being done as part of a massive drive started earlier this year, and around one lakh LED lights have been installed by replacing old ones in the recent months, they said.

news.title: Demolition of illegal structures in Aravali to continue, observes SC
news.para: A bench comprising Justices A M Khanwilkar and Dinesh Maheshwari said that as per previous order of the apex court, the intervenors are supposed to make representation to the concerned authority which will consider them.

news.title: Delayed extension of Jaipur metro corridor making it non-viable
news.para: As the project slips on the state government’s priority list, the Jaipur Metro Rail Corporation (JMRC) hasn’t moved an inch forward.

news.title: People in remote area of Jammu & Kashmir's Rajouri get houses under PMAY
news.para: The people of the far-flung hilly area of Draman Panchayat have also been provided jobs under the MNREGA scheme. Abdul Rehman, Sarpanch said that under the PMAY 200 pucca houses are being constructed here.

news.title: Nuvoco Vistas makes tepid debut on bourses
news.para: ​The scrip, whose issue price was Rs 570 apiece, started trading at Rs 471, which translates to a discount of 17.3 per cent. However, the shares went up in morning trade compared to the opening level and inched up to Rs 538.65 apiece, which is 5.50 per cent lower than the issue price.

news.title: Curbing illegal sand mining a daunting task for Bihar cops
news.para: Illegal sand mining, especially from the Sone river, has been hitting headlines since last two months as government first removed at least 60 officers from field posting and then suspended 35 of them, including IPS officers Sudheer Kumar Porika and Rakesh Kumar Dubey, for their alleged nexus with sand smugglers.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: EoIs invited for flat complex for 18 MLAs
news.para: The apartment complex needs to be within a five km radius of the legislative assembly building, and the period of accommodation will be two years.

news.title: Chandigarh administration seek powers to decide building misuse penalty
news.para: The UT as of now has to submit a proposal related to reducing building misuse charges before the ministry. The traders had even moved the Punjab and Haryana high court on the issue.

news.title: Colonies developed 35 years ago in Jaipur yet to be regularised
news.para: In the absence of lease deeds, residents are facing several problems including availing of loan for construction, land conversion, house expansion and others.

news.title: Thane: FIR against five developers for cheating partners of Rs 9 crore
news.para: ​The accused, who are partners from the same family, by taking investments from the victim family, offered them partnership in several projects but later started avoided giving them proper returns from the profit.

news.title: CIDCO starts geo-tagging land parcels in Navi Mumbai
news.para: The move, apart from helping applicants, will also be an additional step toward efficient digitisation of land records at the sprawling southeastern suburb of India’s commercial capital. With this, Navi Mumbai will be one of the first big cities in the country to initiate the process of the digitisation of land records.

news.title: Kamdhenu Group plans Rs 200 crore investment to expand paints business
news.para: The move will be taken after the demerger of the paints division into a separate entity. The demerger is expected to be completed by November-December this year, he told PTI.

news.title: Mumbai: SRA builders beat pandemic blues with record project nods in two years
news.para: According to data from the SRA, 516 Letters of Intent (LoIs) were issued between March 2019 and April 2021, including those that were re-issued as they were stuck for a long time and 82 new ones.

news.title: Maharashtra: Property registration revenue in July reaches 93% of pre-pandemic level
news.para: The department had registered nearly 1.7 lakh documents in July as compared to 2.6 lakh documents in 2019, but the revenue amount is less by just 7%.
